lyrics.text:
Oh, you silly thing 

I could never ever cut you out 

How could you ever think for a second I was capable?

I won’t go away 

No way

Ever ever 

Oh, your pretty face, shining like it was a second sun 

Over everything

Making life a little brighter babI won’t go away 

No way

Ever ever 

When I placed you into my heart I put you there forever 

Don’t think if I don’t hit you up, I’m gonna forget you 

You’re an evergreen 

Don’t worry, darling

When you fall asleep I hope that you do with open eyes 

Getting all your dreams from living in a little paradise 

That don’t go away

No way 

Ever ever 

 Don’t you think we’ve been through enough to not have to worry?

Don’t ask me what I do for work when you know I’m working 

You’re an evergreen

Don’t worry, darling

Isn’t this real enough?

How do I feel to the touch?

You know that I love you so much I put your whole body on ice 

Put diamonds surrounding your neck but you can still go where you like

Baby don’t take it too far 

You can have everything, I’ll give you the keys to my car

Baby let’s go for a drive 

But baby don’t take it too far  

Let’s run away where we can stay forever
